xtb MOLECULE.sdf --ohess extreme --acc 0.0001 --alpb SOLVENT --chrg CHARGE --input gbsa_extreme.inp --etemp 300 --uhf 0 --iterations 1000 --cycle 10000 --gfn 2 -P CORE --ceasefiles --verbose --strict
#Note that --etemp 300, --uhf 0, and --gfn 2 are default settings for most calculations if the molecule is a closed-shell, neutral system.
`--ceasefiles` is used to	reduces secondary file output (less clutter).
`--verbose` is used to provude detailed screen output for debugging/monitoring.
`--strict` is used to turn all warnings into hard errors. In practice, this means if any non-fatal runtime warning is generated during the calculation, the program will stop immediately instead of completing with a warning message. This will save time from calculating the wrong/incomplete geometry.
